Actually, not true, Query.  There are several other CDs worth of Parker's playing.  One torrent on Isohunt consists of all the band sides on which he performed before he started releasing things under his own name.  A multi-CD set on Mosaic (never torrented, as far as I know) gives all the apocryphal performances recorded by Dean Benedetti.  There are also many other bootlegged performances that were released on smaller labels on LP and later on CD.  This torrent, wonderful as it is, only accounts for about half of what is still extant.
